{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2e38f93b-da0e-44cf-b02a-f7e7276c7dc4","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf the class is in a specific namespace (e.g., `MyApp.Tests.ReportExporterTests`), you can be more precise:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~MyApp.Tests.ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", while `=` means \"equals\".","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b3c0c4bb-aa5e-461c-902d-37655b6a9c00","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":192,"requestId":"702D:1A47AE:708BE:8593B:69F2AE49"},"id":"fbb3e46a-c54f-4d0c-b618-93f5a9ebb491","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:20:13.601Z","parentId":"0392256d-f2e9-4ead-b097-973071041f12"}
